{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Encourage all secondary schools to adopt timetabled, live-streamed lessons.",
        "additional_details": "Live-streamed lessons:\r\n\u2022 Help minimise online distractions for pupils\r\n\u2022 Maintain a consistent standard of teaching\r\n\u2022 Assist in-school and remote learning simultaneously\r\n\u2022 Encourage engagement and feedback\r\n\u2022 Can be recorded and made accessible on demand\r\n\u2022 Are not restricted to a specific class size\r\n\u2022 Promote safer social interaction in a closed online environment\r\n\u2022 Provide a routine and structure to the day\r\n\u2022 Help parents working from home\r\n\u2022 Facilitate a smooth transition when schools reopen",
        "background": "Whilst the use of streaming apps/services has been widely adopted it has not been embraced by all schools. This puts many pupils at a disadvantage. We ask the Government to encourage schools to live-stream lessons for core subjects alongside others where possible and keep to a timetable.",
